HDFS - Hadoop distributed file system
	File system that manages the storage across a network of machines are called distributed file system.
HDFS Suits for::
	Very large files
	Streaming data access
	Commodity hardware
HDFS not suit for::
	Low-latency data access
	Lots of small files
	Multiple writers, arbitrary file modifications
	
HDFS Concepts::

BLOCKS::
	A disk has a block size, which is the minimum amount of data that it can read or write.(512kb)
	HDFS Blocks are larger compared to disk blocks, and the reason is to minimize the seek time.

